 und politische Stoßkraft des postmodernen Romans offenzulegen.  aThe interlocking of the postmodern novel with the sexuality discourse of Freudomarxism, exemplified by Thomas Pynchon and William S. Burroughs.  afunded by Forschungszentrum Historische Geisteswissenschaften  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 0aAmerican fictiony20th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aPostmodernism (Literature)zUnited States. 0aSexual freedom in literature. 0aSexual freedomzUnited StatesxHistory. 4aAmerika. 4aAmerikanistik. 4aFrankfurter Schule. 4aFreudomarxismus. 4aHerbert Marcuse. 4aIdeengeschichte. 4aKulturgeschichte. 4aKörper. 4aLiteratur. 4aLiteraturwissenschaft. 4aNorman O. Brown. 4aPostmoderne. 4aPsychoanalyse. 4aSexualität. 4aSexuelle Befreiung. 4aThomas Pynchon. 4aUSA. 4aWilhelm Reich. 4aWilliam S. Burroughs. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / American / General.2bisacsh  aAmerica.  aAmerican Studies.  aBody.  aCultural History.  aFrankfurt School.  aFreudomarxism.  aHerbert Marcuse.  aHistory of Ideas.  aLiterary Studies.  aLiterature.  aNorman O. Brown.  aPostmodernism.  aPsychoanalysis.  aSexual Liberation.  aSexuality.  aUSA.  aWilhelm Reich.  aWilliam S. Burroughs.2 aForschungszentrum Historische Geisteswissenschaftenefunder.4fnd4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/fnd08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2019 Part 2z978311076669108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2019z978311071956708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019z9783110664232oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural and Area Studies 2019z9783110606348oZDB-23-DKU40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783839448700zCo-access DOI >> click W